# Documentation files are source content - no need to ignore documentation files like CHANGELOG.md, COMMANDS.md, RELEASE_NOTES.md, SETUP_GUIDE.md
# README.md is also source content

# No build artifacts, dependencies, or temporary files detected in changes
# Only documentation files were added/modified

# Therefore, no additional ignore rules are needed beyond what might already exist for general project types

# If this were a typical project, you might want these common rules:
# __pycache__/
# *.pyc
# .env
# .env.local
# .vscode/
# .idea/
# *.log
# .gitignore

# However, since only documentation was changed, keeping .gitignore empty makes sense for this specific case.